{{Quote|You seen that new BT-16?''"<br />"''Yeah, some of the other guys were telling me about it. They say it's&hellip; it's quite a thing to see&hellip;|A stromtrooper and his partner aboard the first Death Star|<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref>}}
The '''BT-16''' was a piece of technology used in the [[Galactic Empire]]. It was considered new<ref name="Episode IV" /> as of [[1 BBY]].<ref name="GA">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas: Updated Edition]]''</ref> When the [[Jedi Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] deactivated the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station|first Death Star's]] [[tractor beam]] to allow the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]'' to leave [[Docking Bay 327]], he overheard two [[stormtrooper]]s conversing about the BT-16.<ref name="Episode IV" />

==Behind the scenes==
The subtitles on [[Disney+]] identifies it as VT-16.<ref name="Episode IV" /> Voice actor [[Sam Witwer]] added lines spoken by stormtroopers in other ''[[Star Wars]]'' films that referenced the scene which mentioned the BT-16 by mentioning the [[T-15]], [[T-16 skyhopper|T-16]], [[T-17]] and [[T-18]].<ref name="Sam Witwer">{{YouTube|video=Z8UdXvynS50|text=Sam Witwer - Matt Lanter - Star Wars Celebration 2022 - DAY 4 Panel|channel=UCX2BSSVDZbk5PrppNQREfTA|name=Super Steve|date=29-05-2022}}</ref> In [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], the BT-16 was a [[BT-16 perimeter droid|perimeter droid]] model.<ref name="Complete">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' Vol. 1</ref>

